text: Old Hen cafe is one of my favourite cafe. It is not a fancy cafe. But is one of those few cafe that still charge reason price. Food is generous portion and delicious. Cafe us clean and comfortable and service personal.

The coffee was okay—smooth but not very strong, and the small cup size left us unsatisfied. On the bright side, the avocado toast was delicious! The big breakfast was decent, though nothing extraordinary.

The café itself is quite cramped; we had to squeeze in to avoid bumping elbows with neighboring diners.

Cosy and compact, 1hr sit in time for dine in. Pretty reasonable for a break in the afternoon.
Ordered a hot dark chocolate, an iced white, buttered corn chowder and apple cinnamon waffles.
Hot chocolate and coffee were standard. Chowder was comforting while the waffles were great. Definitely recco the apple cinnamon waffles!

Cozy breakfast nook tucked in Rangoon.
Sticky date cupcake is moist and not too sweet, paired really well with their coffee.
Their sourdough with butter and egg may be simple but done very well. Love that they that herby butter, really elevated an already good slice of sourdough.
A nice little coffee shop. The avocado on toast with soft boiled egg has delicious as was the cold brew coffee. Staff were friendly and courteous.
